		<credit project="CfPBoK@https://slebok.github.io/cfpbok/"/>
		<div class="right"><a href="index.html"><img src="../sle.png" alt="SLE 2012 SI"></a><br><code>sle2012s/paper06</code></div>
			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2012 SI</a> paper:</span><br><i>Monolithic and modular termination analyses for higher-order attribute grammars</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/LijeshKrishnan.html">Lijesh Krishnan</a>, <a href="../profile/EricVanWyk.html">Eric Van Wyk</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.scico.2014.05.016">10.1016/j.scico.2014.05.016</a></li>
<li>Extended version of <a href="../sle2012/paper03.html"><em>Termination Analysis for Higher-Order Attribute Grammars</em></a> (SLE 2012)</li>
<li><a href="../tag/t5b.html"><span class="tagM">T5B: Language Description Analysis</span></a><ul><li> The paper develops static analyses for attribute grammar specifications (termination of higher-order attribute evaluation), i.e., analysis of language descriptions.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t5d.html"><span class="tagL">T5D: Formal Methods</span></a><ul><li> It provides a sound (though incomplete) termination argument based on term-rewriting abstractions and correctness reasoning.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t1d.html"><span class="tagL">T1D: Composition</span></a><ul><li> The modular analysis is explicitly motivated by independently-developed language extensions and their safe composition.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4a.html"><span class="tagL">T4A: Workbenches</span></a><ul><li> The analyses are implemented in and evaluated within an attribute-grammar system/tooling ecosystem (Silver/ableJ).
</li></ul></li></ul>
		<clear/>
		<footer/>
	</body>
</html>
